<h2>Warm November 2020</h2>
<br><br>
November 2020 was together with 2009 the second warmest November in Europe since 1979, 0.2 &deg;C below the temperature for November 2015. The autumn overall, September, October, November was the warmest on record. European temperatures were 1.9&deg;C above the 1981-2010 average and 0.4&deg;C higher than the average temperature in 2006, which was previously the warmest autumn. Most of Europe saw above average temperatures, but especially the northern part encountered high anomalies (figure 1).
<br><br>
In Scandinavia many temperature records were broken. The highest temperature in Sweden was 18.4&deg;C in Gladhammar, the same value as the previous Swedish November record noted in 1968. In Denmark the highest temperature in November was 17.7&deg;C, the second highest ever measured in Denmark. More than 17&deg;C in November has only be seen three times before in Denmark since 1874. Normal daytime temperatures in November are between 4 and 8&deg;C in Denmark. Finland had a new national record of highest November temperature at Mariehamn Airport on &#197;land Island at 16.6&deg;C.
<br><br>
