<h2>Specific climate indicators for November 2020</h2>
<br><br>
Due to the extraordinary warm spell during this month in Northern Europe, the number of frost days was below the 30-years average(figure 3). Most of the frost days occurred in western Norway and in the Alpine region, which was normal. Ice days (when the temperature is below zero for 24 hours) occurred in the Balkan countries, which were not exceptional. Further ice days were reported in the Pyrenees, which was not exceptional.
