<h2>The weather in November 2020</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
<br><br>
In November temperatures in most parts of Europe were much or exceptionally above the long-term average (figure 6). Temperatures were particularly high in western and northern Europe. In Scandinavia temperatures were 5 degrees or more above average (figure 5). Only in parts of eastern Europe daytime temperatures were below average, although nighttime and daily mean temperatures were above average like in the rest of Europe. Also in most of Europe the temperatures of the coldest night and the warmest day were much or exceptionally much above average (figure 7).
